summary: That was the best part, the dreaming. She dreamed of wolves most every night. A great pack of wolves, with her at the head. She...
text: That was the best part, the dreaming. She dreamed of wolves most every night. A great pack of wolves, with her at the head. She was bigger than any of them, stronger, swifter, faster. She could outrun horses and outfight lions. When she bared her teeth even men would run from her, her belly was never empty long, and her fur kept her warm even when the wind was blowing cold. And her brothers and sisters were with her, many and more of them, fierce and terrible and hers. They would never leave her.
source:
A Storm of Swords

Arya Stark would never ever leave her family. She is a pack animal. She thrives around those she loves. Love motivates her list, not hate.

summary: Good Gendrya Things
title: Good Gendrya Things
body:
They refuse to move to Storm’s End and take over without making themselves properly known to the people there

Before they even get to the castle, they go round talking to the people

Gendry immediately endears himself to a group of children in the town square, and joins in with the game they’re playing.

Arya watches, a smile on her face, and struggles to take in a breath as she realises she wants something she’s never felt safe enough to want.

A pack of her own. Of their own.

summary: She would make much better time on her own, Arya knew, but she could not leave them. They were her pack, her friends, the only...
text: She would make much better time on her own, Arya knew, but she could not leave them. They were her pack, her friends, the only living friends that remained to her, and if not for her they would still be safe at Harrenhal, Gendry sweating at his forge and Hot Pie in the kitchens. If the Mummers catch us, I’ll tell them that I’m Ned Stark’s daughter and sister to the King in the North. I’ll command them to take me to my brother, and to do no harm to Hot Pie and Gendry. They might not believe her, though, and even if they did … Lord Bolton was her brother’s bannerman, but he frightened her all the same. I won’t let them take us, she vowed silently, reaching back over her shoulder to touch the hilt of the sword that Gendry had stolen for her. I won’t.
source:
A Storm of Swords

Remember this every time the show tries to tell us Arya is a lone wolf. She is heartbroken when she thinks they abandoned her

summary: OOOO O O O i have a theory!!!!! feel free to discuss but after watching and thinking about 8x04 again, i think arya saying she’s...
body: OOOO O O O i have a theory!!!!! feel free to discuss but after watching and thinking about 8x04 again, i think arya saying she’s not going back to the North could have a deeper meaning.  I think she rejected Gendry’s proposal because yes she’s not a lady, that’s not her, but also because like she also said, she has unfinished business in the South that’s she’s on her way to deal with right now.  I think she’s going to do whatever her unfinished business is, being to kill Cersei or whatever it may be, but also once that’s taken care of, I think she’s going to go to Storm’s End! Because, like Gendry said, he barely knows how to be a lord or even hold a fork, and I think Arya understands that he doesn’t want her to be a lady, he wants the real Arya. I think she know’s that he was a fool in love and was nervous and babbling and just spilling his heart out to her.  So I think she might go to Storm’s End to maybe propose to Gendry herself, but with the understanding that she will be herself and an equal in the marriage.  I also think she rejected Gendry because, like Jaime and Brienne, if she said yes to him, it would break his heart if she died.  So she broke his heart herself. Like Jaime did to Brienne. Please discuss
